Apologies if this is off the development timeline or out of left field. The psi4 plugin system is excellent, and it's one of the really cool unique features of the package.

One way to make it even better would be if it didn't require having access to the source to compile a plugin. Currently, all the static archives stay inside the object directory and are not installed to `prefix`, which means that when the plugins need to link against psi4, they link against the archives in the object directory, and the psi4 binary embeds the location of the source and build directory to use when generating an example plugin makefile. It would be nice to copy the archives to `$PREFIX/lib` instead.

---
Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:
https://github.com/psi4/psi4public/issues/162
